remarks.format:
## Remarks Call <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs.Dispose> when you are finished using the <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs>. The <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs.Dispose> method leaves the <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs> in an unusable state. After calling <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs.Dispose>, you must release all references to the <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs> so that the garbage collector can reclaim the memory that the <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs> was occupying. For more information, see [Cleaning Up Unmanaged Resources](~/docs/standard/garbage-collection/unmanaged.md) and [Implementing a Dispose Method](~/docs/standard/garbage-collection/implementing-dispose.md).
> [!NOTE] > Always call <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs.Dispose> before you release your last reference to the <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs>. Otherwise, the resources it is using are not freed until the garbage collector calls the <xref:System.Object.Finalize%2A> method of the <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs> object.

remarks.format:
## Remarks This method is called by the <xref:System.Object.Finalize%2A> method. `Dispose()` invokes the protected `Dispose(Boolean)` method with the unnamed Boolean parameter set to `true`. <xref:System.Object.Finalize%2A> invokes `Dispose` with the parameter set to `false`.
When the Boolean parameter is `true`, this method releases all resources held by any managed objects that this <xref:System.Printing.PrintSystemObjectPropertyChangedEventArgs> references. This method invokes the `Dispose()` method of each referenced object.
